cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper presents a new transmission scheme for cognitive radio systems, which involves wireless power transfer and energy harvesting. Information theory concepts are used to analyze the performance of the proposed scheme. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design and analysis of a new cognitive radio system, which involves communication between multiple nodes and a power beacon base station. Networking and internet architecture concepts are relevant to this work. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new system for cognitive radio transmission, which involves energy harvesting and wireless power transfer. Systems and control concepts are relevant to the design and analysis of such systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed cognitive radio system under different channel conditions, which can affect the quality of multimedia transmission. Multimedia concepts are relevant to this work. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, but these concepts are relevant to cognitive radio systems, which need to ensure secure and reliable communication.
